name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
notes:
*************THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC********** 

Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Clark County PH- COVID Vaccine Site

address.street1: Ridgefield High School 2630 S Hillhurst Rd

notes:
The Ridgefield High School vaccination site is providing the Johnson & Johnson vaccine and the Pfizer vaccine. The Johnson & Johnson vaccine requires only one dose; you will not need to return for a second dose. The Pfizer vaccine requires two doses; if this is your first dose, you will need to return for a second dose.

Please do not arrive more than 10 minutes before your scheduled appointment. Arriving too early can lead to longer waiting times. 

You will be asked to remain at the vaccination site for 15 to 30 minutes after being vaccinated. Medical personnel will be monitoring you for possible reactions. Severe reactions are rare. 

What to bring:
•	Identification: If you have identification or some other proof of your date of birth, please bring it. This helps to ensure registration information is accurate. But ID is not required for vaccination. 
•	Face covering: Face coverings must be worn while at the COVID-19 vaccination site. 
•	Please wear a short-sleeved shirt or shirt with loose sleeves that can be pulled up. You will receive your COVID-19 vaccine in your upper arm. 

El lugar de vacunación en la Ridgefield High School está proporcionando la vacuna Johnson &Johnson y la vacuna Pfizer. La vacuna Johnson & Johnson requiere sólo una dosis; usted no tendrá que regresar por una segunda dosis. La vacuna Pfizer requiere dos dosis; si esta es su primera dosis, tendrá que volver para una segunda dosis.

Por favor, no llegue más de 10 minutos antes de su cita. Llegar con demasiada antelación puede causar tiempos de espera más largos.

Se le pedirá que permanezca en el centro de vacunación de 15 a 30 minutos después de ser vacunado. El personal médico le vigilará para detectar posibles reacciones. Las reacciones graves son poco frecuentes.  

Qué debe traer:
•	Identificación: Si tiene un documento de identitificación, o documento con fecha de nacimiento, por favor tráigalo. Esto ayuda a asegurar que la información de registro es correcta. Pero no es necesario presentar un documento de identidad para la vacunación.  
•	Prenda para cubrirse la cara: Debe llevar una prenda para cubrirse la cara mientras esté en el centro de vacunación de COVID-19.  
•	Por favor, lleve una camisa de mangas cortas o una camisa con mangas sueltas que se puedan subir. Usted recibirá la vacuna contra la COVID-19 en la parte superior del brazo.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Olympic Pharmacy and Healthcare Services - COVID Vaccine Venue
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS FOR 2nd DOSE MODERNA VACCINATIONS ONLY**
Please bring your VACCINATION CARD from your first dose vaccination.
Please bring your State ID, and if you have insurance, please bring your insurance card or Medicare B card (red, white and blue card). If you received your first vaccination with us, we will not need a copy of your insurance card.
Please do not come to the clinic if you are not feeling well.
Please wear loose sleeved, short sleeved or sleeveless shirt
When you enter Olympic Pharmacy, please follow COVID clinic signs to the back conference/fitting area. This clinic is not in the pharmacy area.
Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing
Please be prepared to wait 15-30 minutes after vaccination for observation of adverse reactions.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Onestop Medical Clinic - Covid Vaccination Venue
notes:
• Onestop Medical, a Primary Care Clinic is serving the community by administering COVID-19 vaccines as a giving back in the current difficult situation since January 2021. Please DO NOT disrespect our hardworking staff and volunteers. No profanity please.
	
	• Due to the social distancing limitations and limited parking, please plan to arrive NO earlier than 5 Minutes. Please DO NOT park in front of our neighbor’s building; 1316 Central Ave S. The extra public parking is available next door at the Kent Municipal Court (1220 Central Ave S, Kent, WA 98032).
	
	• We ask that for everyone’s safety, please DO NOT visit this vaccination drive without an appointment. Please DO NOT email or call us to inquire, schedule, reschedule, cancel your appointment about COVID-19 Vaccine as we are experiencing extremely high email and call volumes. Please DO NOT book an appointment from the Zocodoc or Onestop Medical's website for COVID-19 Immunization.
	
	• Please schedule your Dose 2 through Prepmod.doh.wa.gov between 21 to 42 (at least 17 days considering grace period) days apart. Please DO NOT laminate the vaccine card. 
 
	• Please remember that you will need to bring your photo ID/Passport, medical insurance card (if insured). If you're receiving your 2nd vaccination, you will be required to bring your vaccination card too.

	• We DO NOT accept any form of payment, donation for COVID-19 vaccine from any patient. Please DO NOT make any payment to the Onestop Medical. If you receive a bill for your COVID vaccine, please contact your insurance company First.
	If you DO NOT have an insurance, no worries and you will still receive your vaccine.
	If you have Insurance a small Admin Fee will be charged to the insurance. The patient DOES NOT PAY for any vaccine related services out-of-pocket  The Admin Fee will be used to help cover a portion of the cost to maintain the staff, PPEs and all medical need.
	
	https://www.doh.wa.gov/Emergencies/COVID19/VaccineInformation/VaccineCost#heading67668
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
